text:
i remember when i was 19 and working in a restaurant. the owner was about to get married. i don’t know how old he was. it doesn’t matter. he would stand next to me and whisper all the things he wanted to do to me. .
.
i remember when i was 20 and i was making out with a guy i thought was so amazing. he wouldn’t believe that i was a virgin and kept pushing and pushing. i said no over and over. he ultimately didn’t force the issue. we fell asleep and he had such a death grip on my fingers that i literally couldn’t untwine. .
.
when i was 21 and walking down the street in the rain and someone grabbed my ass. i said “no” and he laughed at me. .
.
for all the other times and all the other women and men who have said no or felt like they couldn’t. or just didn’t but wish they had. .
.
🖼 @liberaljane

text:
i got "lost" in the other days practice. i cannot describe how deep into meditation i was. i didnt even notice that an hour had gone by. it's the most intense chakra line up i have felt in sometime. i am so thankful for this resource. my mind, body, and spirit are getting better as each day passes. i am not what i once was. mental and physical health problems can create major hurdles. i have belief in myself that i will reshape all of me into what i am meant to be. enjoying my solitude and freedom; i know it's weird to have those 2 things put together and experienced simultaneously to some, but to me it's now a choice. i know i can come and go as i please. that i am not stuck nor prisoner to anything or one. sometimes i need to be reminded of that, but as of late it's been less and less. ---------------------------------------- inside of me,
 almost all of my flowers were dead.  where sinewy stems,  pithy petals,  puffy pollen,  crippled eukaryotic cells cushion and warm a stubborn seed. 🌱🌳💜 #yoga #yogaeverydamnday #relax #yogaflow #poetry #blog #blogger #mindbodysoul #survivor #metoo #mentalhealth #depression #ptsd #spoonie #raynauds #fibromyalgia #fibrowarrior #womenshealth #lgbtq #queer #domesticviolencerecovery #abuserecovery #recovery #healing #writing #writercommunity #inspire #benddontbreak #selfcare

i created our stories matter so that every survivors voice can be heard. this project is an evolving collection i will be working on for awhile and hope to have the first edition completed this year. the final product will be a collaborative journal full of real, raw, eye-opening, heartbreaking, and inspirational stories. and i’m grateful to have licensed psychotherapist @cosmicchristine by my side to help provide a safe place for people to come forward and open up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
オープニングを飾る招待作品はチャン・グンソクの主演作ながら ベルリン映画祭でワールドプレミアされて以来 「#metoo」運動を受けてお蔵入りしていた『人間、空間、時間、そして人間（仮題）』。

text:
i think today i'm going to share part of a monologue i wrote titled 'help' -
lust, love, we think we know  the difference between the two until it's  all too late. 
so what if we kiss? so what if we decide to have sex? hypothetically speaking of course.
we require human connection. basic human connection. a want.. no, a need to be loved, to feel desired. some might even call it a pursuit of happiness.
but it never does work, does it? there's always going to be something missing. lust never seems to satisfy our human desires. if lust was an olympic sport i'd probably be a gold medalist right? casually sleeping with strangers to mask and hide the pains and mistakes of the past. just so i can have some sense of control in your life. is love even real? or is it just a social construct designed to make us feel or think that there's something more to life? a drug created to blind us from a harsh reality of abuse. 
as i lay in bed with a stranger, whose name i still can't remember, i'm possessed by an overwhelming sense of guilt as i recall what it was like to experience this with the first and potentially the only love i've ever had. and i'm reminded of the terrible things that happened just a few years ago. 
i gasp for air. 
a hand is forcibly placed over my mouth, a whisper in my ear. everything is happening so quickly but it only takes a few seconds for me to realize that... oh god, it's happening again
i can feel the life leaving my body, my energies releasing back into the universe and i know. i know that i won't be waking up from this one.
-
-
#writing #writingprompts #monologues #abuse #metoo #writers #english

text: one of the most important releases of the year, “rocking the couch,” available on demand this february from avail films. hollywood titans, harvey weinstein and bill cosby, have been brought to their knees by the #metoo movement. but they did not invent casting couch. the term casting couch has existed for decades. but in 1992, a case against talent agent, wallace kaye, was brought to court by 12 unknown actresses, who braved the loss of their careers, their privacy, and their hollywood dreams. they stepped forward, despite the advice of their union, and brought the case to the police. against all odds, they won, and no one listened. watch the full trailer at http://the-imn.com #imn #undergroundreggie

text:
nous sommes très fiers de vous annoncer que laurence rosier a gagné le prix de l'enseignement et de l'éducation permanente du parlement de la fédération wallonie-bruxelles pour son ouvrage "de l'insulte... aux femmes" 🙏
.
.
.
bienvenue dans l'arène du langage ! nourrie par une foule d'exemples historiques et contemporains, la réflexion de laurence rosier nous amène dans l'univers des insultes, des insulteur.e.s et des insulté.e.s avec raymonde la syndicaliste, george l'écrivaine, nabilla la star de la téléréalité, christiane la ministre mais aussi colette, marguerite duras, audre lorde, margareth thatcher, laurette onkelinx, myriam leroy, christine angot, brigitte macron, les femen, les gameuses... la violence verbale sera passée au crible de l'analyse à travers le genre, les archétypes, les lieux, les règles explicites et implicites de l'injure en société et sur la toile ! 
en filigrane, on lira l'histoire de la "pisseuse": le sobriquet reçu avant la naissance pour déjà (dé)classer la future petite fille...
.
.
.
#180editions #laurencerosier #delinsulteauxfemmes #feminisme #droitdesfemmes #langage #insulte #metoo #essai #genres #instalivre #instabook #book #litterature #bookstagram #booklover #bruxelles #brussel #parlementdelafederationwalloniebruxelles #pfwb

text:
democrats grapple with fairfax assault accusations in #metoo era
#
jenna portnoy reporter covering virginia, maryland and d.c. congressional delegations antonio olivo reporter covering government, politics and demographics in northern virginia february 5 at 6:49 pm the day after lt. gov. justin fairfax (d) denied allegations of sexual misconduct, democrats grappled with how to respond without betraying a rising star in their party or abandoning victims in the #metoo era. nearly all democrats at the state and federal level swiftly called for gov. ralph northam (d) to resign over a racist photo from his 1984 yearbook that became public friday. but lawmakers and party officials interviewed took a more circumspect approach to the allegation against fairfax, which surfaced monday, just three days later. although democrats at the state and national level have been quick to say women should be believed and that all allegations should be investigated, they say they are resisting a rush to judgment. unlike claims of assault against supreme court justice brett m. kavanaugh, former senator al franken (d-minn.), former congressman john conyers jr. (d-mich.) and others, virginia democrats privately note the accuser in the fairfax case has not yet offered evidence she says corroborates her claim. the dilemma shows the trouble they have enforcing a policy…
link: http://metoozoo.com/news/democrats-grapple-with-fairfax-assault-accusations-in-metoo-era/

text:
😢 😤 abomination! 
pope francis has admitted that clerics have sexually abused nuns, and in one case they were kept as sex slaves.

he said in that case his predecessor, pope benedict, was forced to shut down an entire congregation of nuns who were being abused by priests.

it is thought to be the first time that pope francis has acknowledged the sexual abuse of nuns by the clergy.

he said the church was attempting to address the problem but said it was "still going on". pope francis made the comments on tuesday to reporters while on a historic tour of the middle east.

he admitted that priests and bishops had abused nuns, but said the church was aware of the issue and "working on it". "it's a path that we've been on," he said. "pope benedict had the courage to dissolve a female congregation which was at a certain level, because this slavery of women had entered it - slavery, even to the point of sexual slavery - on the part of clerics or the founder." alessandro gisotti of the vatican press office later told cbs news that the order in question had been based in france.

pope francis said sexual abuse of nuns was an ongoing problem but happened largely in "certain congregations, predominantly new ones". last november, the catholic church's global organisation for nuns denounced the "culture of silence and secrecy" that prevented them from speaking out.

just days ago the vatican's women's magazine, women church world, condemned the abuse, saying in some cases nuns were forced to abort priests' children - something catholicism forbids.

the magazine said the #metoo movement meant more women were now coming forward with their stories.

www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-47134033?sthisfb

text:
“in 1970, nearly 50 years ago, i was part of an iconic event and now they’re making a film about it. it’s called ‘misbehaviour’. finding that out has to be one of the most exciting moments of my life. they had the script for 7 years but nobody wanted to buy it until #metoo. my friend sally is being played by keira knightley. rhys ifans is in it, and a new rising star called jesse buckley is playing me. we went to the albert hall, as feminists, to protest against the miss world contest. i’d seen it on the telly since i was a kid. whole families would be involved in this sport of objectifying women. but we thought ‘there’s so much more to a woman’s beauty than just standing there in a swimming suit!' we wanted to get people to stop and ask ‘why does this competition even exist?!’
.
“i was dressed as though i was going to ascot racecourse – in a pink striped velvet coat and a big pink floppy hat, with a large satchel full of rotten veg, bags of flours, smoke bombs and a water-pistol filled with blue dye. i was also 4 months pregnant with our son, who’s grown up to have an enquiring mind and a protesting, caring soul too. bob hope came on to compere and made these dreadful attempts at jokes like ‘i’ve just had to go backstage to feel up the calves, hahaha’. eventually the signal went off – a football rattle – and i started throwing my rotten veg. then all these leaflets started floating down, followed by flour bombs. it looked like snow was raining through the spotlights. we knew it would hit primetime tv in england but it ended up going around the world. we had millions of viewers. that’s how it became iconic. later that night i was arrested after i'd just lit a smoke bomb. i was charged with ‘discharging a missile with intent to endanger the public’ and sent to holloway prison. interestingly, the woman who won it, miss grenada, went back to college later in life to study gender politics.”
.
jo, met in walthamstow.
.

text:
we are not satisfied.
•
"we are not satisfied with flat-lined suicide death numbers", says a director from the air force to @cnn in a recent article that talks about the military confronting the issue with #suicide rates tripling within the us special ops in 2018.
•
according to studies within us military branches, many suicides appear to be related to substance abuse, personal relationship issues or financial problems. suicide is not ok, nor should it be the solution to ending your problems.
•
suicide is not an option. our heart goes out to all #veterans today and those actively serving in any military branch. partner with us today as we acknowledge all those who have served and those actively serving.
•
thank you for your service. thank you for your sacrifice. thank you for our freedom.
•
need help or support? call the veterans and military crisis line: 800-273-8255, press 1.

text:
do you ever sometimes wonder why our high-stress lifestyles have become so normalized? 🤔
.
for nearly my whole life, i have been guilty of sacrificing my health for what society viewed as success.  i had poor eating habits, poor sleeping habits, and a poor mindset (i.e. motivated by fear).
.
overtime i’ve learned that just because something is normalized doesn’t mean that it’s healthy.
.
our health is our most important asset and it’s time to make it our #1 priority🙏
.
in this next blog post, i share over 25 tangible ways to be active, be outdoors, and be with nature🌲
link is in the bio 👍

text:
sex tape | feb 15 @dixonplace | feb 16 @barnesfoundation. link in bio to my website for more info.

on a recent visit to the national portrait gallery i came upon a sculpture by #patriciacronin of two women (her and her partner) embracing. it wasn’t passionate, it was tender. and while the work is titled "memorial to a marriage" and depicts two lesbians who would not have the right to marry for another 10 years, what i saw was a depiction of care that resonated with me and transcended the politics of sexuality and legality. 
if you've seen my shows, this is something a little different. if you've never come before, please come see what it's about. 
plus, tickets so cheap! 2 for $24 at dixon. the bar is open before and after. bring a date, it's #valentinesday2019 weekend.

text: be careful who you choose to have around your child. that same person who you might love and think won’t hurt your child will be the same person to sneak into the room late at night and hurt them. believe your child child when they tell you about what is happening. because you never know how that person who you choose to have around your child can impact them in a big way. im 21 years old and was molested all throughout elementary kindergarten to the 5th told my mother when i was in the 2nd nothing was done. i got a voice in the 6th in the 7th i had to make an adult decision for myself that i didn’t want to be in that house anymore. at a young age i learned that no one will ever have my back, no one truly cares, and that the closet ppl to you will hurt you. i’m 21 and still to this day the abuse affects me i’m very angry, don’t trust, hard to open up, and don’t show affection all that well i don’t cry  like that.  people ask women why we didn’t say anything and that is why no one cares no one does anything. people rather protect the predator instead of the victim people rather put down and shame the victim instead of the predator. i’ve been a victim for 21 years it’s time i become a survivor like these other women i see. i did not post this to get sympathy i posted it to get it off my chest to post the person who had ruined my whole childhood, teens, relationships and friendships i let this person have control over my life for 21 years n i’m not doing it anymore 💯 it has to stop i need to live my life and not be on edge about things. #metoo #womenempowerment #whyididntreport #believewomen #victimblaming

text:
rami malek señala que "no fue agradable" trabajar con bryan singer

el actor se mostró solidario con las personas que acusan al cineasta por abuso sexual

el actor nominado al óscar, rami malek, se pronunció sobre las acusaciones de abuso sexual que surgieron las últimas semanas sobre el director bohemian rhapsody, bryan singer. 
durante un reconocimiento recibido en el festival de cine internacional de santa barbara, malek expresó su apoyo total a las víctimas de cualquier tipo de abuso sexual y se mostró solidario con ellos. "mi corazón está con cualquiera que tenga que vivir algo como lo que he escuchado y lo que está ahí afuera". "es horrible, es notable que esto suceda, puedo apreciar mucho por lo que han pasado y lo difícil que debe ser para ellos. a la luz de la era #metoo, que de alguna manera esto exista después de esto, es una cosa horrible", dijo.

el actor comentó a un periodista de the hollywood reporter que se le hacía difícil hablar sobre el tema durante el rodaje de la película pues intentaba mantenerse centrado en su personaje de freddie mercury, pero que en ningún momento quiso menospreciar los testimonios de las víctimas. "todos merecen una voz y cualquiera que quiera hablar sobre lo que pasó con bryan merece que se escuche su voz", declaró.

malek, quien ya ha ganado un globo de oro y un premio sag por su actuació, se refirió sobre su propia experiencia, aseguró visiblemente conmovido su incomodidad al momento de trabajar con singer, agradeciendo que finalmente fuera despedido antes de terminar la película. "en mi situación con bryan, no fue agradable, en absoluto. y eso es lo que puedo decir al respecto en este momento", sentenció.

singer fue despedido de bohemian rhapsody debido a sus constantes faltas, aunque más adelante la revista the atlantic sacó a la luz las acusaciones de dos hombres que afirman haber sido obligados a tener relaciones sexuales con el cineasta cuando solo tenían 14 y 17 años. 
aunque el director ha renegado de estas declaraciones, no son las primeras, pues hace dos años cesar sanchez-guzman denunció a singer por haberlo violado en un yate en 2003, cuando tenía 17 años.

text:
anyone watch the state of the union last night?! if you did, you would have seen a sea of white worn by congresswomen and their guests to tribute women’s rights, a color used during the women’s suffrage.
.
“we have a different lens and we approach things very differently, and for us, we wanted to show all the young girls across the country, all the young women that the women’s rights movement hasn’t stopped, it’s continued and it’s now in the united states congress. we’re here. a lot of us have been out and about fighting for equal pay, fighting for medicare – for all those things that i think are really important to women. now were actually at a place where women are making those decisions,” rep. rashida tlaib told time during the 2019 state of the union.” @time
.

text:
vie de prof 👩🏼‍🏫
dans le cadre de mon parcours #metoo, je propose différents textes et supports aux élèves. après le visionnage de clip, de documentaires, l'écoute des musiques de @angele_vl  et @aliceontheroof, je leur demande de retrouver des informations dans des livres et des textes. 📚
bah oui, la compétence abordée est quand même l'uaa1: rechercher l'information. c'est dans ce but que je leur prête les deux tomes des #culottées. d'après ceux-ci, après un travail de recherche dans des ouvrages, ils se serviront de ces bd humoristiques pour raconter la vie d'une des femmes présentées. je leur laisserai le choix de celle qu'ils préfèrent et le travail sera formatif mais j'ai l'espoir que cela me permette de voir leurs difficultés à choisir les informations pertinentes (ou le manque de difficultés) de manière plus amusante qu'avec un texte plat et savant.

text:
« p o e m »
.
.
.
darling, you got everything you wanted,
then why so sad? 
those tears you shed for something years ago
you did get something better, didn't you? 
why it's presence is killing you inside? 
why isn't your starving desire satisfied? 
people call you selfish, 
but you're only looking for a place somewhere familiar
you wished for a rose, but all you got were thorns 
but somehow, whilst watching yourself bleed
you called the pain your home
.
.
.
//ayesha fatimah

text:
public speaking is listed as american's number-one fear, before death and loneliness.. .
.
growing up i definitely was one of the quietest kids in the room, introvert you can say, always shy away from attention and confrontation.
.
.
so trust me when i tell you this was not easy, standing and telling our story in front of almost 8k people.
.
. 
sweaty, nervous, feeling like wanting to throw up and excited all in one but knowing that in order to get to the next level, you have to build up the courage to get it done. every level there will be another obstacle that you will have to learn to overcome... feel the fear and do it anyway. .
.
. 📸 cred: @alexiscruz427 .

text:
папа римский: монахини в католической церкви подвергались сексуальному насилию
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
папа римский франциск подтвердил, что монахини в католической церкви подвергались сексуальному насилию. домогательства совершались самими священниками, пишет tut.by. папа также отметил, что эта проблема имеет место быть и сейчас.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
это заявление стало первым официальным признанием церкви в столь щепетильном вопросе. несмотря на то, что подобные случаи уже известны общественности и являются фактами, ранее католики «в сане» предпочитали об этом молчать. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
франциск уверил, что церковь ищет решение этой проблемы. о результатах, правда, говорить пока рано: случаи продолжают и продолжают повторяться. к ним причастны, кстати, не только рядовые священники, но и те, кто занимает верхушки религиозной иерархии, – епископы. известны также истории о том, как монахинь держали в сексуальном рабстве, а одно монашеское объединение ликвидировали по той причине, что служительниц там регулярно насиловали. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
кроме того, женский журнал women church world, который издаётся в ватикане, тоже высказался по этому поводу. он осудил насилие в церкви, напомнив, что некоторых жертв домогательств даже принуждали делать аборт, что осуждается верующими людьми. есть мнение, что обсуждению этой трагедии поспособствовало движение #metoo.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
time (kaaala) | yoga teacher = hustle, grit and impeccable time management. the stereotype of yoga teacher as spaced out is largely unfounded. 4-7 classes per day with no assistant, requires; scheduling, people skills, organization. planning a training program requires knowledge of the physical body, deep understanding of history and philosophy even more people skills, marketing skills, writing skills, negotiating skills. foresight plus talent! 
i’m deep in the hustle for 15 years. making time to practice, mediate, eat right and walk this path in integrity require a lot of focus and very little room for errors. 
one yoga teacher becomes the pr dept, hr, accounting, marketing/ sales, health/wellness, therapist, life coach, priest/rabbi/shaman, philosopher, historian, movement specialist, anatomy and physiology teacher, exercise fitness coach, comedian, dj...that’s just the job. then there’s mother, friend, girlfriend, yogi.

there have been years the practice felt like an arm of a large beast. i grew resentful of the marketing required and the little time i had to practice and the cult/clique feeling i got from so many studios or systems. 
fortunately that’s shifted again, as i’ve fallen in love with yoga again. 
i’ve got an entirely new take on the system. in large part this has to do with spending some real time in india but also has to do with the guru take down and the uprising of the #metoo movement ushered in by my sisters calling out sexism and inequality in this realm . 
additionally, new understandings around movement and science has lifted this tradition into the current century. 
these changes are helping to lift tradition out of the shadowy influences of religion, classicism and sexism. it’s an exciting time.
photo credits to 🙏 julie dohrman @shaktiyogany

text:
lauren clark was cooling down from a jog nearly six years ago when she spotted a man in the distance. she quickened her pace, hurried past him and, for a moment, considered crossing the street. her fear seemed irrational — paranoid, even — until the threat became real. the man grabbed the slender 27-year-old hairstylist from behind, thrust his hand between her legs and covered her mouth. he slammed her body to the sidewalk. rape seemed imminent. death, quite possible. clark flipped from her stomach onto her back and clawed the man’s face. her fingernails dug into his skin and tore off his eyeglasses. the man punched her in the face, grabbed her phone and sprinted away. the man was caught just minutes later by police, who linked him to an attack against another woman earlier that night. with fresh scratches on his face, he confessed.
•
he was a stranger in the dark who attacked washington, d.c.’s women when they were alone and vulnerable. this was a statistical anomaly in the world of sex crimes, where most attackers know their victims and the majority of assaults never result in criminal charges. clark was a prosecutor’s dream. after identifying the man at the crime scene, she was eager to speak her mind in court. she was unusually vigilant from the start, gathering her own information through police reports and court hearings. altogether, the man admitted to assaulting six women in the district of columbia. but he would spend years avoiding major punishment and rising among the ranks as a chef at some of the area’s top restaurants.
•
clark spent seconds fighting him. she would spend years fighting for justice afterward. “i feel like this case was handed to every department of the justice system on a silver platter,” clark said, telling her story publicly for the first time. listen to clark’s story on @washingtonpost’s podcast “post reports” through the link in our bio. (photo by carolyn van houten @washingtonpost)

text:
"erstmal ins gesicht spucken." ich stehe am bahnhof, warte auf meinen zug und unweit neben mir stehen vier jungs. ich sage bewusst jungs, weil sie in meinen augen nicht älter als 16 oder 17 jahre alt sind und für mich aussehen, wie herandwachsende jungs (ich möchte hier auch nicht zu sehr political correctness walten lassen). die vier unterhalten sich darüber, dass ein kumpel ihnen erzählt hat, dass er bald ein date hat. auf eine frage an diesen kumpel, was er denn mit dem mädel mache, wenn sie sich treffen, antwortete er, nach der aussage einer der jungs mit folgendem satz: "erstmal ins gesicht spucken."
die vier reagieren erstmal entsetzt, verfallen dann aber ziemlich direkt in großes lachen und wiederholen diesen satz permanent. es scheint schon fast, als würden sie ihren kumpel zwar irgendwie als verrückt erklären aber gleichzeitig auch ein wenig feiern für diese antwort.
ich bin mir sicher, dass sich keiner der vier sich bewusst über die eigentliche bedeutung dieses satzes ist und jetzt mag an sich vll denken, dass sie ja eher ihren kumpel auslachen, aber genau an dieser stelle und mit diesem gedanken fängt vertuschung und herunterspielen von diskriminierung an! die reaktion der jungs hätte eine andere sein sollen!
#metoo #womensvoice #equalrights #equalsociety #gleichberechtigung #sprache

"erstmal ins gesicht spucken." ich stehe am bahnhof, wae auf meinen zug und unweit neben mir stehen vier jungs. ich sage bewusst jungs, weil sie in meinen augen nicht älter als 16 oder 17 jahre alt sind und für mich aussehen, wie herandwachsende jungs (ich möchte hier auch nicht zu sehr political correctness walten lassen). die vier unterhalten sich darüber, dass ein kumpel ihnen erzählt hat, dass er bald ein date hat. auf eine frage an diesen kumpel, was er denn mit dem mädel mache, wenn sie sich treffen, antwoete er, nach der aussage einer der jungs mit folgendem satz: "erstmal ins gesicht spucken."
die vier reagieren erstmal entsetzt, verfallen dann aber ziemlich direkt in großes lachen und wiederholen diesen satz permanent. es scheint schon fast, als würden sie ihren kumpel zwar irgendwie als verrückt erklären aber gleichzeitig auch ein wenig feiern für diese antwo.
ich bin mir sicher, dass sich keiner der vier sich bewusst über die eigentliche bedeutung dieses satzes ist und jetzt mag an sich vll denken, dass sie ja eher ihren kumpel auslachen, aber genau an dieser stelle und mit diesem gedanken fängt veuschung und herunterspielen von diskriminierung an! die reaktion der jungs hätte eine andere sein sollen!

text_retweet:
day 3: its not okay #itsnotokay •
 #repost @monachalabi “have you been thinking about false accusations lately? if so, here are some important facts:

1. since 1989 (when us records on this topic began) there are only 319 cases where men convicted of sexual assault were exonerated because it turned out they were falsely accused.
2. false rape accusations are rare. there are three decent studies on this topic (see below) - estimates range from 2.1% to 7.1% of the accusations that are reported being false (don’t forget, most rapes are never reported). for this graphic, i took the midpoint then followed the statistics through to make an estimate about whether individuals faced criminal consequences as a result of these allegations.
3. what planet are you on if you think that it’s common for people to make this shit up? #believewomen

sources: department of justice, office of justice programs, bureau of justice statistics, national crime victimization survey, 2010-2014 (2015); national incident-based reporting system, 2012-2014 (2015); felony defendants in large urban counties, 2009 (2013). heenan, m., & murray, s. (2006). study of reported rapes in victoria 2000-2003: summary research report. retrieved from the state of victoria (australia), department of human services: lonsway, k. a., archambault, j., & lisak, d. (2009). false reports: moving beyond the issue to successfully investigate and prosecute non-stranger sexual assault. the voice, 3(1), 1-11. national registry of exonerations” ✏️ @monachalabi •

text:
“i don’t think heavenly father wants you to just endure this life.” - stacy taniguchi
.
i had so much fun pulling out my old scrapbook from the semester that stacy tanaguchi was one of my byu professors. it was the same semester i lived at aspen grove with a small handful of other recreation management students.
.
his stories were always amazing! from escaping flood planes at the last second to being a guide for tom cruise, he always had us on the edge of our seats.
.
but his stories were so much more than that! he tied them into life and they became inspiring. he was able to motivate us all to reach a little further and be a little more.
.
i literally squealed with delight when the byu magazine showed up and he was on the cover.
.
here he is again! using his stories to motivate you. me. everyone. to chase down your dreams and thrive!
.
in regards to his stories, his life, he says, “it was not just haphazard. i was very intentional about what i wanted in this life.”
.
everyone should take a few minutes, click on the last link in my bio and read his article! i promise you it will get you thinking! it will inspire you! and before you know it, you’ll have an amazing list of things you just know you’re going to accomplish some day.
.
and then, you’re going to get to work and start making them happen! 😉
.
and as a side note - i know this is a long shot - but if you know any of the people in any of these photos, please share this with them. i would love to reconnect!

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members acculding there farthers, brothers and uncles.
-
@abhasinghlawyer said
"it reflects poorly on the law and order situation of rajasthan, it reflects poorly on the constitution of india that a young couple was in love and wanting to get married in gujarat was brought back to banswara where they were beaten by villagers, were stripped naked and paraded when nobody come to help them,"
"a case should be registered under the new criminal law amendment act 2013 where provision 354 b makes the stripping of women cognizable and non ballialble," -
@saswatishosh 
said, "the panchayat went to such an extent that they could not fathom the relationship. how can the administration intervene in such incidents? we cannot tolerate medieval diktats in the modern way of life."
-

all of the years that i spent bearing my untold story were  almost as damaging as my story. 
yes, it’s hard, humiliating and shameful to tell your story. yes, family and friends will walk away from you. however, there is great healing in telling our story. there are others that need to hear our story. they need to know they are not alone. 
they need to know there is hope!
telling my story every chance i get ❤️

text:
wo fängt diskriminierung gegen frauen an? und wo hört sie auf? war sie schon immer da oder wurde sie erschaffen von menschen. von frauen, die sich alles diskriminierende vll. nur einbilden, oder von frauen, die ihre "natürlichen" stellung nicht akzeptien wollen, oder wurde sie vll. eher von männern erschaffen, die nicht verstanden haben, dass eine mögliche körperliche überlegenheit nicht automatisch auch geistige überlegenheit bedeutet? oder gibt es ganz andere gründe?
eigentlich ist es schon beinahe egal, welchen ursprung diese ungleichstellung von frauen hat. unabdinglich ist, dass diskriminierung in jeglicher form, auch gegenüber frauen eine der negativsten und abscheulichsten seiten der menschen ist. sie existiert immer noch und spätestens seit #metoo ist sie in das bewusstsein von fast jeder frau gerückt! -hoffentlich
ich möchte auf dieser seite über meine fast alltäglichen gedanken zum thema diskriminierung von frauen und gleichberechtigung schreiben. möchte darstellen, wie alltäglich und fast schon selbstverständlich wir mit dieser benachteiligung leben, welche formen sie hat und auch auf welche art und weise von uns allen versucht wird, diskriminierende momente und situationen unter anderen gesichtspunkten zu rechtfertigen und somit weiterhin salonfähig zu machen.

text:
"he is a good provider"...
many victims tell us that when they disclosed their abuse to their family, the family didn't believe them or they defended the abuser by trying to the convince the victim that their abuser had good qualities that should somehow overshadow their sexually abusive criminal behavior. "he is a good provider" is a common response that families recite in defense of the abuser. however, it is a lie! a good provider is one who understands their responsibility to not only financially support their family and possibly their extended family, but they also understand their responsibility to provide physical and emotional support. a good provider protects those in their care and within their circle of influence from all harm. a good provider nurtures the total wellbeing of the children in their care and within their circle of influence, and they would never inflict trauma on them by sexually abusing them. if you've been sexually abused and your family's response is to protect the abuser simply because he pays the bills in the house or financially supports your extended  family, they are sending a clear message that they are willing to sacrifice your wellbeing for their personal comfort. they are in essence asking, and sometimes even demanding, that you remain silent about your abuse in order to maintain everyone else's comfort and wellbeing. however, we say stand in your truth! we stand with you! we believe you! and, we can tell you that he is not a good provider! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #superbowl

text_retweet:
#repost from @museblognaija with @regram.app ... ’i was a victim too’ – uche jombo speaks on sexual assault in nollywood
.
.
the 39-year-old actress, screen writer & producer, made this disclosure in an interview with hiptv while speaking on the widespread allegations of sexual assault on upcoming actresses. “i’ve been in that kind of situation twice during my starting days,” she said. “i rehearsed for almost two weeks only to come next and find that someone else was reading my role because i declined the request to ‘see me’ (for sex). “i wept seriously, i was hurt but four to five years later, i made it big.” explaining how she survived and maintained her stance at the time, jombo said: “it is personal integrity. in my days, we move on when we’re denied opportunities for refusing to give in to sexual demands. “sometimes, it’s your individual strength, drive and process that matters. what takes some six months to accomplish might take others six years. “are you ready to wait for your time or you just want a shortcut that leads to no long-lasting opportunity? if you want the shortcut, chances are that there are people willing to give it.” jombo said people who engage in such acts should be called out explaining that this would force nollywood recruiters and opportunity givers who indulge in such acts to “be humans again”. .
.
#museblognaija #uchejombo #nollywood #metoo

text:
vaticano aclara declaración del papa sobre esclavitud sexual

ciudad del vaticano (ap) — el vaticano aclaró el miércoles las declaraciones del papa francisco acerca de lo que llamó la “esclavitud sexual” en una congregación de monjas francesas, al afirmar que se refería a un abuso de poder reflejado en casos de abuso sexual.

francisco mencionó el caso en la víspera, cuando respondía a una pregunta acerca del abuso sexual de monjas por sacerdotes durante una conferencia de prensa en el avión papal al regresar de emiratos árabes unidos. fue la primera vez que el papa habló públicamente sobre el abuso sexual de monjas por parte de sacerdotes y obispos. enfatizó que la santa sede enfrenta el problema desde hace tiempo y piensa hacer más.

el vocero del vaticano, alessandro gisotti, dijo que francisco “habló de ‘esclavitud sexual’ para significar la ‘manipulación’ o un tipo de abuso de poder que se refleja en el abuso sexual”. la comunidad de san juan reconoció en 2013 que su difunto fundador se había conducido “en formas contrarias a la castidad” con mujeres de la orden, según el diario católico francés la croix. el papa benedicto xvi disolvió una rama de la congregación.

el asunto ha salido a la luz con las medidas de la iglesia para frenar el abuso sexual contra menores de edad y el reconocimiento, inspirado por el movimiento #metoo, de que los adultos pueden ser víctimas de abuso cuando existe un desequilibrio del poder en una relación. el año pasado, the associated press y otros medios informaron sobre el abuso cometido contra monjas en india, áfrica, europa y sudamérica, prueba de que el problema no se limita a una zona geográfica.

en noviembre, la unión internacional de superioras generales, que representa a todas las órdenes religiosas católicas de mujeres, denunció públicamente la “cultura del silencio y secreto” que impide a las monjas hablar públicamente y las exhortó a denunciar los abusos a sus superiores y la policía. adicionalmente, la semana pasada, el suplemento femenino del diario vaticano l’osservatore romano identificó como el culpable a la cultura del clero todopoderoso.

la revista “mujer iglesia mundo” observó que el escándalo tiene un coro

haveit is an art collective created by two set of sisters (alketa sylaj & lola sylaj, hana qena & vesa qena) who try to illustrate their daily struggle in a patriarchal society. in recent years haveit has made number of street performances in kosovo and abroad, tackling issues that are remaining taboos across the balkans, such as domestic violence, gender identity or war’s rapes.

text:
i want you to look at this picture below. 
does it make you uncomfortable?
does it make you sad?
angry?
how do you feel after seeing this? 
i am disgusted, i am heartbroken, i am angry, i am filled with rage and sadness.
let me spit some facts at you. 1 in 5 girls will be sexually abused before their 18th birthday, and 1 in 20 boys will be abused. 
in a matter of 1 year(study is from 2010), studies show that 16% of american teens were sexually abused. (ages 14-17)
children are most vulnerable to sexual abuse between the ages of 7-12
this is disgusting. there are so many options out there to help prevent your children and other children around you from sexual abuse.
i thoroughly encourage you to check out defendinnocence.org and read up on facts and how you can protect your children. 
if you are a survivor of childhood sexual abuse, you are not alone. i implore you to go to youniquefoundation.org and apply for a free haven retreat where you will get treatment and therapy to get the help you rightfully deserve. 
if you’d like more info on any of this, please message me, i have a plethora of knowledge on this subject that i’d love to share with you all. #childhoodsexualabuse #csa #sexualabuse #abuseawareness #metoo #savethechildren #makearipple #defendinnocence #youniquefoundation #savethebabies

text:
we are all 'prostitutes' (was it churchill that said it) to a certain degree; we educate ourselves to the best level we can and then sell ourselves to the highest bidder based on what we bring to the table. 
i am trying to do my business as ethically as i can because..... i have to eat, pay bills,  look after my family and home like anyone else.

they've made me an offer.... with a gagging order. thank you,  but no. nobody really needs to know about shit and banana skins or anything else... but ....i am a baby of the windrush. not all of our parents were able to tell their story about the passage here and the racism they faced. 
i am the child of a generation that experienced 'no dogs,  no irish. no blacks!' doesn't anyone want to hear about michael who didn't want any of the black secretaries working as his pa, he'd rather pick a less qualified and less experienced person? 
doesn't anyone want to hear about the other one who thinks it's amusing to call a child 'black poopoo' or music of a different culture 'monkey music.... '

if we don't tell our story it's as if we were never here.  i've received accolades and made people money so i know i was here. i've also been used and abused.... and damaged... so i know i was definitely here.

victim support have called. i have retold what i can recall. yes. i was definitely here.

odw  6.2.19 (c)

text:
//
i could swear 
it was yesterday 
just a while ago 
i could swear 
it was yesterday 
i learnt to let go 
and unlearnt
the pain of holding on
to the things that are
no longer mine to call 
i could swear 
it was yesterday 
i pieced myself together
and promised not to fall
i could swear 
it was yesterday 
i swallowed my ache
because in that moment
it was more
than i could take
i could swear 
it was yesterday 
i was smiling
and it didn’t feel like a sin
i could swear 
i’d made peace
with the course of the wind
that pushed back the tears
i’d been carrying around 
since yesterday 
i could swear 
it was just yesterday 
i didn’t need a reason to be happy 
but it’s today 
i don’t need one to be sad
__________
everyday doesn’t have to be a great one. you can have your lows and still go on just fine. i don’t get why some people make happiness a necessity when it really is just a part of life. it comes and goes. and it should be considered perfectly alright if someone’s just not feeling it.
“cheer up”
“you get one shot”
“life’s short”
son, we know. and we’re making the most of it by feeling both extremes of the human emotion. although we tend to incline towards the heavier ones, do not tell us what to feel and what not to. i’m sorry if i do not relate to your ideas of fun or happiness. and yeah this is what i’m passionate about– feeling everything to the point that it breaks my heart. and this is also what i want the world to be okay with. i’m very much content with my misery,  thank you. (next)

text:
update-event sold out | sisterhood: fierce and funny women - pop-up event ⠀
⠀
in the week of international women's day, join us for a special event as three of the country’s most in-demand speakers and writers come to henley for a frank, funny and fierce look at what it means to be a woman in 2019.⠀
⠀
on monday 4th march, journalist @jessicajonzen will be joined in the stunning setting of the @riverandrowingmuseum by @thedaisybee, @helenlederer and @nikita_gill to discuss everything from #metoo and period poverty to female friendship and the women that inspire them.⠀
⠀
this is an event not to be missed so order your tickets now via the link in our bio (tickets are £12.50 plus booking fee). ⠀
⠀
about the speakers:⠀
⠀
daisy buchanan returns to henley the week her second book ‘sisterhood: a love letter to the women who have shaped me’ is published. the much-anticipated follow-up to ‘how to be a grown up’, it celebrates the ways in which women connect with each other. grazia’s agony aunt turned reality tv expert, daisy also hosts the brilliant ‘you’re booked’ podcast and is a regular guest on radio 4, sky news and good morning britain.⠀
⠀
comedian and author helen lederer has been making us laugh on screen for over three decades, from ‘absolutely fabulous’ to ‘naked video’. her most recent book ‘losing it’ was nominated for the wodehouse prize. she has recently launched the comedy women in print prize, giving female comedy writing the recognition it deserves.⠀
⠀
with widespread acclaim for her collections ‘your soul is a river’ and ‘wild embers’, nikita gill is one of the most popular young voices in poetry around the world, with almost 500,000 followers on instagram. her latest book ‘fierce fairytales’ reimagines classic fairytales as empowering messages for adult women.⠀
⠀
⠀

text:
everytime we ask "what was she wearing?" "was she sober?" "where was she going?"... every time we tell victims to be silent because "what would it do to the family?" "what would people think?" and all the questions we ask abused women, we supply the abuser with an excuse so they do not have to go through the trouble of thinking of one. they can find comfort in those questions and be absolved of accountability for their actions. he will not have to say he knew what he was doing was wrong. he will not have to say he knew he could get away with it. he won't have to say a thing at all because society would have said everything he needs to seem less guilty.

text:
it's the time of the year we host the annual festival of journalism department of kamala nehru college "journo junction". journo junction has been a perfect blend of informative seminars, ruminating events, mouth watering food and most importantly fun.

the theme for journo junction'19 is "media and marginalities: issues and concerns". the year 2018 had some of the major milestones of the decade.
the #metoo movement gave visibility to the sheer number of cases of sexual harrassment and assault. it was able to call out some prominent public figures who were involved in the crimes.
section 377 was revoked by the supreme court which decriminalized homosexuality. the trans bill contrastive denies fair opportunities to the lgbtq+ community.

the annual festival aims at revisiting these events and have a discussion around them.

text:
you are so smart.  sometimes this is not a good thing - especially when our smarts are used against ourselves.  get out of your head! you are able to overthink any situation, problem or thought to the point where you come up short.  you have such compassion and caring for others but struggle to do so for yourself.  get out of your head. 
how?  talk to someone you trust.  when you say things out loud you can better see the distortions than when you stay in your head.  i know it is scary to share.  i know it is scary to be real.  if you don’t yet feel ready to verbally share with a friend, write down those thoughts and share with your therapist or coach so you can work through them.  let’s use our intelligence and smarts to help ourselves,  not to hurt or limit us 💜

text:
first essay in our #metoo series. 
how photographer mahesh shantaram got away with #metoo⁠ ⁠ “shantaram begins his facebook post by vehemently declaring his liberal, feminist credentials. even shantaram’s instagram page carries the slogan “fuck patriarchy,” although it isn’t quite clear how he intends or proposes to do that given that his career is largely based on the photographing of that most patriarchal of social institutions, the heterosexual marriage. he insists that he has “been a vocal upholder of feminist causes and a fighter of the good fight” but no evidence of this claim is offered or available for us to see. he goes on to argue, “i know that no means no, and i know to take no for an answer,” echoing the now popular “no means no” slogan associated with anti-rape movements.

so why does he begin here? he wants the reader to know that he is a man who is incapable of doing what the women have accused him of doing. these assertions of feminist warrior-hood and of knowing when no means no assume that those who fight the feminist fight cannot be sexual harassers or those who stand with feminists cannot be abusers or those who “fight the good fight” cannot be predators.” by @suchitravijayan . read&share! @project_polis, @indiametoo, #art, #photography, #india, #timesup
https://www.thepolisproject.com/how-an-artist-gets-away-with-metoo-autopsy-of-an-apology/
name: THE POLIS PROJECT, Inc

.

text:
my tattoo that i’ve had for a yr on the 13th. a lot for some reason don’t know i have this. they immediately are like oh i love your dragon fly tattoo. 
but right now, do me a favor... cover those wings, what do you see?
i have a semi colon as the body. representing the finish of me surviving years of abuse. but yet, me still knowing that my story isn’t over yet. 
i’m a 2 time survivor of rape, around 12-14 yrs of mental, emotional and physical abuse survivor. 
so this is why we never judge a book by its cover... ask my friends or anyone and i seem like the happiest person in the world, but behind that i hold yrs of damage. but i’m done letting that control me. i will take anyone down who try’s to control me or be “slick”. “i am smarter than you think” 
#semicolontattoo #semicolonproject #survivor #metoomovement #metoo #weightlossjourney #mystoryisntoveryet #confidenceiskey

the  album was met with a lot of bias by other male artists who must have lied to by someone who did not want anyone to recognize that a woman could be successful as a producer with her own production company/record label. many injustices were done to #classysilhouette.

5. we don’t know why someone would be this hateful to slander someone & try to defame someone’s character this way. it was a very hurtful thing but we didn’t allow that to stop progress.  #classysilhouetteproductions has released 2 hiphop albums since then

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

text:
join us for our poetry evening on tonight featuring
james arthur, gale burns and natalie whittaker. #brookespoetry #waterstonesoxford #cafewoxford #poetryevening #waterstonesevents #oxfordevents 
james arthur was born in connecticut and grew up in canada. he is the author of the poetry collection the suicide's son, forthcoming in spring 2019 from véhicule press. his debut, charms against lightning, is available from copper canyon press. his chapbook hundred acre wood was published in 2018 by anstruther press. 
gale burns is a london-based prizewinning poet who is a writer-in-residence at both the sydenham arts festival and kingston university, where he teaches creative writing. he convenes the long-running shuffle poetry series in london, and was a 2012 hawthornden fellow. he is widely published with three pamphlets and a collection just out from eyewear entitled mute house.

natalie whittaker is from south east london, where she works as a secondary school teacher. her poems have been published in poetry news, brittle star, aesthetica creative writing annual, #metoo: a women’s poetry anthology and south bank poetry. natalie was awarded second place in the poetry on the lake short poem competition 2018 and the oxford brookes international poetry competition 2017. her debut pamphlet from ignitionpress is called shadow dogs.

i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
negative impact of digital marketing⠀
⠀
while the benefits are easy to see, another important consideration when going digital with your marketing plan is the negative impact of digital marketing. it’s easy to think, “what could possibly go wrong with online advertising?” well, when more people are viewing marketing content, there’s always the fear (or there should be) that the wrong message could be perceived. if marketers aren’t conscious of what’s going on around them, it’s easy to put out a message that can be #misinterpreted. for example, consider the #metoo movement.⠀
⠀
if a marketer was unaware of the movement (perhaps they’ve been hiding under a rock) and ran a banner ad on facebook with some humor about something that could even slightly, in some far-off universe, be considered sexist, it could be the death of that company. while that might sound severe, consider the line, “once it’s been on the internet, it’s out there forever.” once an ad has run that can be affiliated with a company and is interpreted in an offensive manner, it’s out there, never to be retracted. it’s often death by digital suicide for the company behind the message.⠀
while there are always negatives with any marketing strategy, the impact of digital marketing on businesses has, overall, been a positive one. with more access to a broader audience, digital marketing illuminates businesses in ways that were once impossible, saving businesses time, money, and bringing in new customers like never before.⠀
⠀
⠀
⠀

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
un si petit objet peut tellement t’aider 😍 c’était kiné ce matin ! .
.
ça fait bien longtemps que je ne t’ai pas parlé de super juju aka juliette aka ma kiné du sport 💗✨
.
.
j’ai énormément de chance de travailler avec elle 🙏🏻 nous nous sommes rencontrées il y a pile 3 ans et j’étais profondément abîmée de partout ☹️
.
.
elle m’a expliqué comment mon corps fonctionne, elle m’a expliqué comment me positionner, me renforcer, m’approprier mon corps. elle m’a vu parfois pleurer et toujours persévérer 💪🏻
.
.
je dispose de tant de connaissance aujourd’hui grâce à elle 🔥
.
.
le reste c’est de la pratique encore et encore. c’est équilibrer la force et l’étirement. c’est retirer les couches émotionnelles qui enveloppent certaines parties de mon corps ou qui se sont carrément glissées à l’intérieur de lui. .
.
c’est difficile ? oui. ça demande des efforts ? oui. c’est inconfortable ? oui. est-ce que je pourrais vendre le truc un peu mieux ? non. .
.
la vérité c’est que rester dans un corps qui souffre et qui a mal est horrible. et honnêtement ça peut clairement faire péter un câble. .
.
la vérité c’est qu’endurer de la douleur pour transformer mes chairs de l’intérieur de mon corps, c’est faire face à la douleur du trauma. ça permet ensuite de la faire sortir, ça permet de trouver ce bénéfice. .
.
s’il n’y avait pas un bénéfice derrière, crois tu vraiment que je continuerais ? .
.
le bénéfice c’est quoi ? c’est me sentir enfin l i b r e ❤️❤️❤️ libre dans mon corps, libre dans ma tête, libre de récupérer enfin ce qui m’a été ôté enfant : consentir à ce que je veux pour moi, pour mon corps. libre d’effectuer un mouvement que la douleur m’empêchait de faire quelques jours, mois ou années avant. voilà quelles sont mes victoires ✊🏻🔥
.
.
autour de moi je rencontre beaucoup de jugements sur ce que je fais, mais une chose est sûre : il n’y a que moi qui vis dans mon corps. personne n’a vécu les viols, les coups, les strangulations, les mots, les silences, les fausses couches, les opérations chirurgicales à répétition que j’ai vécues. [suite en commentaire]

la vérité c’est que rester dans un corps qui souffre et qui a mal est horrible. et honnêtement ça peut clairement faire péter un câble. .
.
la vérité c’est qu’endurer de la douleur pour transformer mes chairs de l’intérieur de mon corps, c’est faire face à la douleur du trauma. ça permet ensuite de la faire soir, ça permet de trouver ce bénéfice. .
.
s’il n’y avait pas un bénéfice derrière, crois tu vraiment que je continuerais ? .
.
le bénéfice c’est quoi ? c’est me sentir enfin l i b r e ❤️❤️❤️ libre dans mon corps, libre dans ma tête, libre de récupérer enfin ce qui m’a été ôté enfant : consentir à ce que je veux pour moi, pour mon corps. libre d’effectuer un mouvement que la douleur m’empêchait de faire quelques jours, mois ou années avant. voilà quelles sont mes victoires ✊🏻🔥
.
.
autour de moi je rencontre beaucoup de jugements sur ce que je fais, mais une chose est sûre : il n’y a que moi qui vis dans mon corps. personne n’a vécu les viols, les coups, les strangulations, les mots, les silences, les fausses couches, les opérations chirurgicales à répétition que j’ai vécues. [suite en commentaire]

text:
kristen roupenian was not what i expected. i heard her interviewed for elizabeth day’s podcast how to fail last night at foyles and it opened the question of fiction as a craft rather than a sort of journaling.

i’m in favour of raw vulnerability in writing and that’s the real difference for me between literary fiction and genre fiction, rather than anything about snobbery. but roupenian’s story of “the grey area”, cat person (if you haven’t read it, it’s free to read on the new yorker), seemed like a confessional tale, to the point where a lot of readers thought it was a personal account.

but she’s not a college student, she’s in her late 30s. this matters because what she wrote about in cat person was hard to achieve despite perhaps not appearing that way. roupenian deserves praise for her craft because that’s precisely how she got to the human truth of her story. if you don’t recall the era before me too, no one spoke about grey areas unless it was to vindicate aggressors. i think cat person will appear on timelines of the me too movement in the future, because it examines something that was previously rendered invisible. that’s what capturing the zeitgeist in fiction is all about.

#bookstagram #shortstories #catperson #kristenroupenian #metoo #feministliterature #americanliterature #bookspodcasts #howtofail #howtowrite

i was so overwhelmed when i got to find out that the founder was a man. my interest rate grew by 101%. it built a new level of motivation and i longed to meet with a man of excellence.

he's the most accommodating, loving and supportive founder you can meet anywhere in the world. he's love for leadership and women excelling is so beautiful.

he's always willing to listen to you without sentiments, no matter who you are.. whenever  i see him,my heart says your dreams are valid young woman.

thanks for being an exceptional man.
thanks for making a difference.
thanks for pushing us to excel regardless of the hurdles.
thanks for being a women's man
thanks for the book:african women of worth- it's the most inspiring piece i have read this year..

thanks so much sir  @elishaattai

text:
с 30 января по 1 февраля 2019 года в волгограде прошло первенство 🇷🇺 россии по легкой атлетике среди юношей и девушек до 18 лет. ⠀
в соревнованиях приняли участие более 580 спортсменов из всех регионов россии. 😎
⠀
воспитанник сшор по легкой атлетике «мгфсо» москомспорта александр соловьев с результатом 4 метра 80 сантиметров завоевал бронзовую награду в прыжках с шестом. ⠀
🏃‍♂️🏃‍♂️🏃‍♂️🏃‍♂️
⠀
3 февраля 2019 года в москве прошли традиционные всероссийские соревнования по легкой атлетике «русская зима». ❄️
⠀
спортсменка сшор по легкой атлетике «мгфсо» москомспорта ольга муллина с результатом 4 метра 45 сантиметров стала третьей в прыжках с шестом. 🔥 ⠀

neue podcastfolge! 🎧❤️
diese folge ist ein super wichtiges und persönliches herzensanliegen von mir, denn in dieser 4. episode von "bright&bold" wird es um deinen selbstwert gehen.
.
💕du wirst lernen, was genau der selbstwert für uns menschen ist, welche elemente er beinhaltet, mit welchen kernthemen der persönlichkeitsentwicklung er verwandt ist und wie er einzuornen ist.
💕dazu bekommst du wertvolle und auch herausfordernde fragen, die du für dich selbst beantworten darfst, um auf heilsame weise an deinem selbstwert zu arbeiten.
.
in dieser folge möchte ich dich auch daran teilhaben lassen, welche erfahrungen ich persönlich mit meinem selbstwert in der verbindung mit sexuellen missbrauch gemacht habe.
.
ich freue mich, wenn meine erfahrungen dir helfen können, einen gesunden selbstwert für dich aufzubauen. vielleicht bist du ja selbst auch von dem thema betroffen und kannst anhand meiner erkenntnisse wertvolle aha-momente sammeln.
.
wenn dir dieses thema aber doch zu persönlich sein sollte oder du befürchtest, dass es dir in deiner gefühlswelt zu nahe kommen könnte, dann spule in der episode einfach direkt nach der "triggerwarnung" zu minute 27. so kannst du dann trotzdem alle wertvollen basics für dich mitnehmen, auch wenn du nicht in meine persönliche geschichte eintauchen magst.
.
❤️höre hier bitte auf deine innere stimme und entscheide eigenständig!
.
ich freue mich riesig, diese folge mit dir teilen zu dürfen und ich bin zugegebenermaßen auch echt etwas aufgeregt! ich wünsche dir viel freude, reiche erkenntnis und ermutigende, positive gedanken mit dieser podcastfolge!
.
herzlichst, deine rebecca
.

denne novellesamlingen dufter ikke bare av blomster, altså! cat person (på norsk: kattemenneske) er new yorker-novellen som ble delt i rekordfart i kjølvannet av #metoo . hun møter han. de ender i senga, selv om han er en sjokkerende dårlig kysser. selv om han frastøter henne. selv om han gjør henne lattermild. så hvorfor går hun ikke bare?
«du vet at du vil» er mørke noveller om kjønn og makt. og selv om de til tider kan være ganske så ubehagelig, anbefales de på det sterkeste👊

text:
papa françesku pranon abuzimin dhe skllavërinë seksuale të murgeshave nga priftërinjtë katolikë

papa françesku ka pranuar se abuzimi seksual i murgeshave nga priftërinjtë katolikë dhe “skllavëria seksuale” është një problem i vazhdueshëm në kishën katolike, por thekson se vatikani po “punon për ta ndalur këtë fenomen”. “nuk mund të them kjo nuk po ndodh në shtëpinë time. është e vërtetë,” tha papa kur një gazetar i tregoi një artikull të kohëve të fundit, në revistën e grave të vatikanit për abuzimin seksual të murgeshave. “a duhet të bëjmë më shumë? po. a jemi të gatshëm? po. ne kemi punuar për këtë për një kohë të gjatë. ne kemi pezulluar edhe disa priftërinj për shkak të kësaj.”, shtoi papa françesku.

i pyetur nëse ai po planifikonte të thërriste një konferencë të peshkopëve, të ngjashme me samitin e këtij muaji për të trajtuar abuzimin seksual të klerikëve me fëmijët, papa nuk u përgjigj. “dua të shkoj përpara. ne po punojmë për këtë”, përsëriti ai.

papa françesku vlerësoi paraardhësin e tij, papa benedikti, për shpërndarjen e një kongregacioni të murgeshave “për shkak se skllavëria ishte bërë pjesë e saj, madje edhe skllavëria seksuale nga ana e priftërinjve”. një drejtor i shtypit në vatikan, konfirmoi se papa françesku po i referohej komunitetit të shën jean në francë, i cili u shpërnda gjatë vitit të parë të benediktit si papë, në 2005-ën.

ndërgjegjësimi i publikut për abuzimin seksual të murgeshave nga priftërinjtë erdhi si pasojë e papritur e lëvizjes “#metoo”, e cila nisi dhe në mesin e motrave katolike vitin e kaluar.

ky skandal erdhi në një kohë të keqe për kishën katolike, e cila ishte zhytur tashmë në një skandal të abuzimit seksual të fëmijëve që përfshinte mijëra priftërinj dhe madje edhe më shumë viktima.

papa françesku u ka bërë thirrje palëve fajtore që të kthehen dhe të “përgatiten për drejtësinë hyjnore”, ndërsa këtë muaj është thirrur edhe një samit i peshkopëve për të trajtuar problemin.

vini re: ky artikull është pronë intelektuale e rt/ përshtati në shqip hashtag.al

papa françesku vlerësoi paraardhësin e tij, papa benedikti, për shpërndarjen e një kongregacioni të murgeshave “për shkak se skllavëria ishte bërë pjesë e saj, madje edhe skllavëria seksuale nga ana e priftërinjve”. një drejtor i shtypit në vatikan, konfirmoi se papa françesku po i referohej komunitetit të shën jean në francë, i cili u shpërnda gjatë vitit të parë të benediktit si papë, në 2005-ën.

ndërgjegjësimi i publikut për abuzimin seksual të murgeshave nga priftërinjtë erdhi si pasojë e papritur e lëvizjes “ e cila nisi dhe në mesin e motrave katolike vitin e kaluar.

ky skandal erdhi në një kohë të keqe për kishën katolike, e cila ishte zhytur tashmë në një skandal të abuzimit seksual të fëmijëve që përfshinte mijëra priftërinj dhe madje edhe më shumë viktima.

papa françesku u ka bërë thirrje palëve fajtore që të kthehen dhe të “përgatiten për drejtësinë hyjnore”, ndërsa këtë muaj është thirrur edhe një samit i peshkopëve për të trajtuar problemin.

vini re: ky aikull është pronë intelektuale e / përshtati në shqip hashtag.al

text:
international day of zero tolerance for female genital mutilation (fgm).more than 130 million women worldwide have undergone fgm. fgm occurs in parts of africa and asia, in societies with various cultures and religions. i had never heard of fgm, let alone did i realize that it is commonplace in many countries. fgm encompasses a variety of procedures that involve the cutting of female genitals, known to some as female circumcision. the most extreme case of this is where the clitoris and inner labia are removed, and the outer labia are sewn together. a hole is left for urinating and menstruation. in some cultures,this happens during infancy; in others, adolescent girls up until their marrying age (14-16). most commonly, girls are 7-8 when they are cut.
the point of doing this is to ensure that women are pure before marriage. it’s become so culturally accepted, that some women won’t allow their sons to get married to a woman who isn’t circumcised. it’s seen as shameful to not be wanted for marriage in many cultures, and thus, women are inevitably pressured into feeling as though they want and need this procedure done. in case you were wondering, women are cut back open on their wedding night.
aside from the obvious consequences of not having sterile medical equipment (many women have it done by another woman in the village who is assigned to do it for all young girls) there are a plethora of issues that can arise from this. women can die of something as simple as a menstrual cycle, if there is no way for the blood to be properly extricated from the body.when you really think about it, if a woman wants to have fgm done, she should be able to. taking away women’s choices is what we’re trying to combat. and telling women that they can’t do something is pretty contrary to what we’re trying to achieve by the means of equality. but the other thing is that women who think they want this done may not realize that there is any other option. #fgm #endfgm #hearmetoo #humanrights  #metoo #genderequality #violenceagainstwomen #standup #childmarriage #sexual #physicalabuse #feminist #humanrightsforall #wellbeing #heforshe #bhfyp #unwomen  #timesup #sisterhood #feminist #feminism

text:
konnichiwa minna 
annyeong 
juste une histoire comme il doit y avoir plein d'autres... juste une histoire de #metoo... avec ce hashtags, ce dont on a le plus parlé, ce sont des femmes qui ont été abusées... il semble que les hommes aient un droit de parole limité sur ce sujet... peut-être parce que cela touche à leur virilité... ils souffrent donc en silence... jusqu'à n'en plus pouvoir... et puis un jour une histoire sort... la partie émergée de l'iceberg... ateen est un tout jeune groupe de kpop encore peu connu. 6 de ses 10 membres ont subi du harcèlement sexuel de la part de la femme du ceo de leur agence... cette agence qui est censée les protéger et les emmener vers la voie du succès en échange de leur complète abnégation, d'un travail de fou sans repos, d'une absence de vie privée... une agence qui leur a fait des promesses mais qui les a trompés... ils ont tous moins de trente ans et sont déjà détruits en partie... psychologiquement... des blessures profondes qui ne cicatriseront certainement jamais complètement... j'ai mal pour eux... mais je ne peux m'empêcher de penser que dans d'autres agences, cachés bien à l'abri de leur aura, de leur pouvoir, de leur puissance, certains font subir la même chose à d'autres artistes... et ça me rend tellement triste cette part d'ombre... ça me fend le cœur... et ça me donne envie de vomir sur la mentalité de certaines personnes... alors si vous voulez leur montrer votre soutien, partagez les deux hashtags suivants sur tous les réseaux sociaux :

#justiceforateen
#wesupportyouateen

et je leur souhaite beaucoup de courage... 🌦️🌸💮❄️💔🇰🇷💔❄️💮🌸🌦️

text:
please read the photos and the description📢

disclaimer: this is purely my personal experience, this is my story no one else’s.

i want to address something that has happened to me not only this past weekend but at the beginning of this year as well . . . this is not easy for me, but i would like to share my truth.

the reason i am addressing this publicly is because i read neil kaplan’s tweets that he posted sunday night after the convention and i am disgusted. i am appalled that he is gaining support for “having courage” and “standing up for what’s right”. i was willing to keep all of this closeted since it was handled privately within the convention staff, but i will never allow someone so hateful and inappropriate get away with being a hypocrite. i encourage anyone who has felt the way i felt, who has been places in uncomfortable and inappropriate predator-like situation to handle your issues like an adult. go through the proper channels when addressing situation so controversial. there are ways to handle things privately, posting publicly is not always the answer. i am posting publicly because i believe the public should be aware of my story and how easy it is for someone with a following to lie to you and convince you that they are nothing but kind and respectful when in fact they are not. don’t always believe what you read.

#vicmignogna @nekappix #sigh #innapropriate #unprofessional #speakingup #mytruth #metoo #neilkaplan

text:
we're still reeling from our celebration of sohaila abdulali's grounbreaking 'what we talk about when we talk about rape' at @g5afoundation! the conversation was opened by our very own @dizibot, and sohaila explained her journey into the writing of her book, along with her self-identification as a "brown muslim immigrant rape survivor". we talked about #theshamegene, the process of explaining rape culture to children, and what the role of men could be in combating it. [side note: it's not our job as women to explain this to anyone]

additionally, we read out our contest winners & had readings from the book by our own @nixter18 & sohaila herself! the evening ended with some post-event mingling & chatter - thank you all for being such a fabulous audience, we were absolutely loving the vibes throughout! icymi, here are a few glimpses from our evening. keep following us to stay tuned for more #madebywomen events coming your way!

i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
when you realise that maybe you're not as ok as you thought.... this was my reaction when someone i went to school with, and was part of it being such a horrendous experience for me, was mentioned in our group chat. she's got a lovely career now, hence why she popped up on my friend's facebook as a public figure.

you might ask why i'm sharing this publicly after being publicly shamed at school. well i want people to know the lasting effects of bullying, sexual assault and the lack of action by a school that's left me like this 20 years later. if just one person who has had/is currently having a similar experience reads this and seeks help then it will be worth it. do not feel that experiences like this are your fault. you are not to blame for other people's c***y behaviour.

it's experiences like this that make #metoo and the campaigns against bullying so crucial to protect today's vulnerable people so that they don't end up like me.

#metoo #bullying #notok #mentalillness #speakout

text:
female art shows - 2019
a woman’s world 
week 14

this week i read an article from the guardian. it discussed how 2018 was a good year for female artists. galleries and museums celebrated 100 years since british women won the right to vote, with exhibitions and events to commemorate this. but it questions whether now the hype has died down, will it continue to improve for female artists around the world. 
a link to the article is found on my website under the blog section. 
currently, i am on week 14 of my yearly project called a woman’s world, where i create a piece of work once a week in response to a feminist related story or issue. i post every wednesday.

text:
monkeying around japan 🐒🗻
-
had a blast hanging around the macaques. they are an incredibly intelligent species of primates with the ability to invent new behaviors and then pass them on from generation to generation.
-
the macaques of jigokudani developed their love for the hot springs after a young macaque had discovered the enjoyment of taking a dip in the hot waters on a cold winter's day. since then the troop of 20-30 macaques have been frequently observed enjoying these hot waters.

text:
lifes blood
mixed media on canvas
2019 
the damage didn’t come all at once drenched in life’s blood my body atrophied blistered and cracked

this shattered vessel still aches from the first time it was touched from where he tore me apart with his teeth 
plucking his way through each and every rib he dug his way deep into my chest cavity searching for the beating 
my heart was still warm and full when he tore it out on that rose covered couch 
i can still feel the coldness of the touch 
each finger sending vibrations harshly coursing through my bursting veins 
but as i allow myself to break open the tingling and the fear go running 
the healing begins. 
i remind myself that the tearing opens

opens you up to let something fill you once again 
something better 
brighter 
#metoo
