text:
in so many unofficial ways, lexi was a lifeline for me. she was a dog that, for so many of her good years, was so in tune with me emotionally. she was never a big cuddler but on my worst days, she crawled on top of me and laid with me until the #bleakness past. and when i was started to get furious, she would nudge me until i focused on her and the agitation melted away.
loosing lexi last summer scared me because i thought i was loosing an important #soulmate that helped me work through the darkness.
i did loose a soulmate but little did i know that my independent, wilful #corgi would somehow know there was a silent job to do after lexi's passing. like lexi, she nudges me when the agitation grows. she pokes my arms after a bad episode and lies her muzzle on them. and, when i need her comfort, she is there - #always. without being asked, she just seems to know.
how lucky am i to have these creatures in my life who know me so well and who are so willing to #support and help me.
today was not a great day and when i finally got home, she was right there. she wedges herself in so tightly ❤️ she keeps the #darkness at bay. 
#thankgodfordogs #speakthetruth #bpd #ilovemydog #metoo #survivor #unconditionallove #grateful

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members acculding there farthers, brothers and uncles.
-
@abhasinghlawyer said
"it reflects poorly on the law and order situation of rajasthan, it reflects poorly on the constitution of india that a young couple was in love and wanting to get married in gujarat was brought back to banswara where they were beaten by villagers, were stripped naked and paraded when nobody come to help them,"
"a case should be registered under the new criminal law amendment act 2013 where provision 354 b makes the stripping of women cognizable and non ballialble," -
@saswatishosh

text:
tw: sexual assault/rape 
so for some ungodly reason, there are people out there who find the #metoo movement funny and take it as a joke, or just spam "not all men!!" well no shit, not all men rape, not all women rape, not everyone has been sexually assaulted or harrased. but i have, so speaking from experience and how it's shaped me, shouting not all men and shit like "oh you're making it up" or "you waited so long to speak up obviously you didn't mind" well ha, one reason, like others have stated, we don't speak up out of fear. i was sexually assaulted by two of my siblings. one who is almost twice my age and one only two years older than me. i didn't, and still haven't really, spoken up out of fear. the one almost half my age has anger problems and is babied by my mother. if i tried to speak up against him i'd be brushed asided or he'd be called in to ask if i'm speaking the truth. which would only make it worse. since it's been so long the police aren't an option. he sexually assaulted me three times. with the one two years older than me, she had sexually assaulted me countless times telling me it's okay since we were both girls and siblings. speaking up against her would lead to the same scenario of being accused of making it up and the police again aren't an option since it's been so long.  another reason is that, it's been too long since it happened. the police don't want to listen to us after it's been a certain amount of time, they brush us off for waiting so long because we couldn't. for the longest time i wanted to forget it ever happened but that isn't possible. it never is, sure getting justice helps but that doesn't make it go away. doesn't make the pain and the nightmares and the overall feeling go away, it just numbs it.

text_retweet:
#metoo and the cultural sector in the nordics

just over a year ago the #metoo movement spread across the world. this also arrived to the nordics. last monday there was a kick off organised in helsinki of a series of seminars carried out by the nordic council of ministers in all the nordic countries and self-governing regions in order to raise the question, prevent and combat sexual assault and harassment and to share initiatives and best practice. 
ekvalitas malin hade the hounor to moderate this kick-off seminar that conserned questions as: how did the #metoo movement look in the cultural sector in the nordics, which similarities and differences can be identified? what actions has been taken to tackle the problem and how can we learn from each other?

front figure for the seminars will be the swedish author, journalist and tv &radio host and producer alexandra pascalidou. 
the line up for the event was welcoming words by director ola kellgren nordic culture point 
the scope and significance of the #metoo movement by alexandra pascalidou

arepost on sexual harrassment in the film and theatre industry in finland was presented by adjunct professor of labour and social law jaana paanetoja

these talks was commented by:
director general riitta kaivosoja, ministry of education and culture 
head of legal affairs lottaliina pokkinen, finnish musicians’ union
actor tobias zilliacus 
the second nordic guest on the seminar was  chair kristine karåla øren, norske dansekunstnere that had an speach on
the impact of #metoo in norway

the ombudsman for equality, jukka maarianvaara talked about the role of employers, institutions and society in tackling sexual harassment 
their speaches was commented by:
tanja auvinen, director of the gender equality unit at ministry of social affairs and health
ylva perera, chair for the feminist magazine asta

what a afternoon! great line up, great speakers and discussions.

do not miss the chance to watch it online!👌

text:
first essay in our #metoo series. 
how photographer mahesh shantaram got away with #metoo⁠ ⁠ “shantaram begins his facebook post by vehemently declaring his liberal, feminist credentials. even shantaram’s instagram page carries the slogan “fuck patriarchy,” although it isn’t quite clear how he intends or proposes to do that given that his career is largely based on the photographing of that most patriarchal of social institutions, the heterosexual marriage. he insists that he has “been a vocal upholder of feminist causes and a fighter of the good fight” but no evidence of this claim is offered or available for us to see. he goes on to argue, “i know that no means no, and i know to take no for an answer,” echoing the now popular “no means no” slogan associated with anti-rape movements.

so why does he begin here? he wants the reader to know that he is a man who is incapable of doing what the women have accused him of doing. these assertions of feminist warrior-hood and of knowing when no means no assume that those who fight the feminist fight cannot be sexual harassers or those who stand with feminists cannot be abusers or those who “fight the good fight” cannot be predators.” by @suchitravijayan . read&share! @project_polis, @indiametoo, #art, #photography, #india, #timesup
https://www.thepolisproject.com/how-an-artist-gets-away-with-metoo-autopsy-of-an-apology/

rp @peacebyvegan i think i haven’t really been clear about this in my content so far. i talk a lot about the animals that we eat - but not as often about all other animals.

the extent to which animals are exploited is insane, and they don’t just include those that we eat.
-
eating a cake with eggs seems a lot more innocent than eating a burger or a piece of bacon, but that only plays out in our perception and the stories we tell ourselves.
-
if you care about animals, oppose all forms of animal exploitation, not just the ones that are outwardly obvious ✌🏼

text:
this makes me uncomfortable. but i feel that it’s important to talk about. i happened to be visiting my friend at the same time her brother was visiting and we all went to a party together. towards the end of the night, my purse got stolen and i was really upset so i decided to go back to her place. he was also tired and wanted to go back so we shared an uber while my friend stayed at the party. we had been drinking so as soon as we got in the car, i closed my eyes and rested my head on the window. then i started to feel his hands trying to pry my thighs apart. no matter how hard i was squeezing them together. i was so mortified that i kept pretending i was asleep because who..does..that...to someone...who’s..sleeping. i thought if i was asleep he would stop. well he didn’t... and every time he got a little too “close” i would “fake wake up” or move around and he would stop touching me. cause he didn’t want me to catch him. i texted my friend saying “doesn’t your brother have a girlfriend?” trying to hint at what was happening.. that i didn’t feel safe with him alone in the apartment. instead she replied like this followed by “have fun getting yourself to the airport tomorrow.” nothing even happened but i cried the entire next day and felt so dumb because i could’ve easily said “no.” but i was sacrificing my comfort to save him from embarrassment. i didn’t want to hurt my friends feelings and tell her that her brother was trying to molest me. the next day she still didn’t believe me.. she told our friends who were also on the fence if i was telling the truth or not. she asked him what happened and he said “i was just trying to make her feel better about her purse.” then she asked him to drive me to the airport and i was incapable of making eye contact and had anxiety the entire ride. sexual assault predators can be your brother. father. uncle. friend. we have to stick together and believe one another. •

•
•

text: i know i’m late posting about the follow up to the circles for change event, but i’ve just been taking it all in the change it has brought about. i’m grateful for the opportunity to share part of my story publicly. that was probably one of the hardest things to do i’m not going to front but it was so rewarding and more healing came from it. y’all, all we have to give is our story, our truth, our  experiences. share it. stand it. what happened to you is not who are. own it only you can!! let god use you. less of you more of god. be gods vessel! hurt people heal people. don’t inflict that same pain you’ve experienced on someone else. it is purpose behind your pain, you will see the result of that once you choose to deal and heal. understand that your voice is valuable do something with it. advocate for those who don’t know or can’t for themselves. most importantly 🗣you are valuable and you matter you are loved! #share #spreadloveandlight #speakupandout #metoo

text:
for all the broken hearts out there ... look inward to heal that place that has been left feeling like a brutal punch to gut and to gain clarity needed to see beyond the pain and see the possibilities in its purpose. 
i hope this helps you to know that the sun will shine again so you’ll feel it... the ability to smile and laugh returns...
the capacity to love will return too because it’s always there... it’s just been a state of shock and needs sensuality of self care and self love to come back online. 💕
i hope this poem reboots you and fills you with hope in healing. 🤗
it gets better, i promise. the pain and confusion can’t last forever my lovelies. 💕
i love you! i believe in you! i honor you! i got you! 💋peace ✌️ love 💕 and light 😇💋 💋
#brokenheart #love 💋
**************
love’s chaos
i want my heart back, what’s left of it, 
is not enough to survive on.

you were so much of my life, that it feels like i can’t breathe from the collapse of the empty space. 
i never paved the road that didn’t include you, 
because you were my long road home when i said, “i do”. all i can see is you, 
when i stare in my face, 
and worry about how i’m supposed to get through.
as our life, the life we once knew,
is now gone, but not without a trace.
so many memories of me and the man i once called my boo.

imprints in my soul and mind those torment me too, my whole world revolved around pleasing you. 
now it’s me, myself and i that i’m forced to face. 
but all i can i see, are the memories of me and you.

so i have to love that broken part of me now, for loving her is the way for me to once again see my face and claim my space.

with this understanding from a new place, please know, 
i thank you for the lessons and mirror of you as i watch you go.

you showed me the holes i had to tend to, to heal me and and get back in my own heart space, for that i am grateful for you.

the crushing loss forced me to wander lost in time, running from the memories of your face, 
but i now emerge to begin healing this hole left by you, embracing myself from a self love space.
so for that i say thank you, bless you, wishing you too find forgiveness and your own peaceful place.~c.frazier💋
name: Candice💞Wellness With Candice

text:
this flower girl will called “the flirt” “you were smiling and flirting with me” 
apparently a smile is an invitation.  my smile tells them i want them.  my smile tells them they are entitled.  entitled to touch me. because i was smiling i wanted them physically.  and when my actions and words speak otherwise they’ll ignore me because before i was smiling. the smile gives permission. it invited them in and said i wanted them. and when my hands reposition theirs they will laugh with a smile and say “your too much”. we will wrestle in flirtation.  it’s ok because we are smiling to hide our embarrassment.  he will be embarrassed i’m fighting him off. i’ll be embarrassed i put myself in yet another jeopardizing position. 
did i go on a date? or is this the worlds most polite assault? 
if i reject him he won’t give me a chance to even see if he likes me.  if i allow his aggressive lack of discipline will i even like him anymore?
no one wants a loose woman. 
no one likes a prude. 
sexuality is your power. 
having sex labels you promiscuous. .
.
you were smiling. you were flirting. you don’t mean what you say.  you just play the nice girl routine. because for some reason he feels entitled to your power. he feels entitled to your value. -you shouldn’t smile so much. your giving them the wrong idea. -this is your fault. -you were flirting and invited his hands with your company. -but your also too picky. -you have bad taste in men. -and your standards are too high. -don’t be in a room alone with a man. -don’t be so guarded. -don’t be so quick to judge. -don’t be so trusting. -don’t be completely yourself right off the bat. -honesty is important. -that’s a little too honest. -always be yourself. 🌻
🌻

apparently a smile is an invitation.  my smile tells them i want them.  my smile tells them they are entitled.  entitled to touch me. because i was smiling i wanted them physically.  and when my actions and words speak otherwise they’ll ignore me because before i was smiling. the smile gives permission. it invited them in and said i wanted them. and when my hands reposition theirs they will laugh with a smile and say “your too much”. we will wrestle in flirtation.  it’s ok because we are smiling to hide our embarrassment.  he will be embarrassed i’m fighting him off. i’ll be embarrassed i put myself in yet another jeopardizing position. 
did i go on a date? or is this the worlds most polite assault? 
if i reject him he won’t give me a chance to even see if he likes me.  if i allow his aggressive lack of discipline will i even like him anymore?
no one wants a loose woman. 
no one likes a prude. 
sexuality is your power. 
having sex labels you promiscuous. .
.
you were smiling. you were flirting. you don’t mean what you say.  you just play the nice girl routine. because for some reason he feels entitled to your power. he feels entitled to your value. -you shouldn’t smile so much. your giving them the wrong idea. -this is your fault. -you were flirting and invited his hands with your company. -but your also too picky. -you have bad taste in men. -and your standards are too high. -don’t be in a room alone with a man. -don’t be so guarded. -don’t be so quick to judge. -don’t be so trusting. -don’t be completely yourself right off the bat. -honesty is important. -that’s a little too honest. -always be yourself. 🌻
🌻

text: tonight i had the deepest honour of speaking at the @projectfword event: forgiveness in the #metoo movement 🙏 in a q&a style, myself and another courageous survivor had the opportunity to share our stories, our perspectives on forgiveness, our unfiltered heart-visions for this world regarding this complex topic 🍃 i rarely share my story of sexual assault in such detail anymore... while i honour the painful seed that gave birth to such flowering/movement/creation, this deep dive into the details doesn’t always serve. however, it was truly an empowering gift and a humbling opportunity to share my reality, my raw humanness, my struggle and my trauma transmutation in such a grounded & real way. this was not a presentation, it was a conversation. gratitude for this room/this organization, such a beautiful embodiment of social transformation meeting spirit celebration ✨ deep reverence for the opportunity & capacity to sit in this seat of voice.  wholly inspired by the resilience of my sisters, the magic of male-bodied allies, the solidarity within stories, the courageousness of leaders creating spaces like this 💚thank you thank you for hearing, holding, loving me. stepping out of my own way to let the earth nourishing magic flow through.
name: Marlee Liss

text:
la rosa siempre ha sido el símbolo por excelencia de la sexualidad femenina.
en los primeros cultos a la divinidad femenina, los cinco pétalos de la rosa representaban los cinco estados de la vida de la mujer:  el nacimiento, la menstruación, el alumbramiento, la menopausia y la muerte.
el capullo de la rosa abierta se parece a los genitales femeninos, por donde la humanidad llega a este mundo.
la rosa es por excelencia el símbolo del secreto guardado, ya que es una de las escasas flores que se encierran en su propio corazón y cuando abre su corola, está en la hora de la muerte.🌷
. . .
. . .

text_retweet:
keputusan ugm untuk menyelesaikan kasus pelecehan seksual yang dialami agni (bukan nama sebenarnya) dengan cara 'kekeluargaan' sangat mengecewakan.

pertama, terminologi 'kekeluargaan' artinya menyelesaikan suatu permasalahan secara tertutup dan jauh dari perhatian publik. hal ini semakin memperkuat budaya bahwa pemerkosaan atau pelecehan seksual adalah sesuatu yang tabu dan harus ditutup-tutupi.

kedua, semakin tabu isu ini dibingkai, semakin sulit bagi korban untuk bersuara. korban pelecehan seksual menjadi takut untuk mengungkapkan kebenaran karena khawatir dianggap mempermalukan dirinya, keluarga, atau institusi tempatnya bernaung.

ketiga, semakin sulit korban bersuara, maka semakin leluasa pelaku untuk mengulangi hal serupa. predator seksual akan merasa mendapat perlindungan kultural (karena masyarakat menolak membicarakan isu kekerasan seksual) dan institusional (karena keluarga/institusi enggan memaparkan secara terbuka isu yang dianggap 'aib'). kalau menurut permen ristekdikti nomor 1 tahun 2016, pemberhentian rektor dapat dilakukan oleh menristekdikti. tolong ini panut mulyono, rektor ugm, dicopot. terima kasih.
.
.
.
.

text: i think it's important to address, how were ourselves, and can grow and change and progress, but keeping loved ones in mind is important, especially on the road. days like this, now that the polar vortex is over, i miss my family, the ones i selected throughout the road, that weren't greedy abusers. home; there's been an issue through a place i know that is holding it down right now, a place i found after 2 years that was weirdly symmetrical to my deranged actual friends and family. the competitive capitalist nature is not good. profiting from pain isn't respectable behavior. no ones better than anyone and can't really walk in each others shoes, yet making eachother aware of issues; not silencing us, not trying to speak over another human, like you know them. i hate the i'm the best mentality, where's the we make each other better, throughout our communities, if that's not the way it's going, should probably be ended, no matter who it is. i'm not the best with communication, it gets frustrating, although i try. i miss the miller's, i love the people i actually spent time with and they didn't throw me away, on the way. also it's hard to determine sometimes, but i know some people in this community are genuine, although i'm not putting my life in anyone's hands fully, ever, my life belongs to me, especially until there's moments of personhood to establish and understand and grow from. "those who have gone before us, can inspire us to greater heights." fritz #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors

text:
there is much said about benefits of yoga & meditation on our wellbeing. i personally have been practising kundalini yoga on & off for over 10 years. every time i do it, i literally feel how my brain rewires 🧠
⠀⠀ _____________________
⠀⠀
the research supports my perception. for example, in the study for depression, it was found that after just 3 months of kundalini yoga practice, the plasma serotonin, melatonin & glutamine levels are increased along with lowering of urinary-5-hydroxyindole acetic acid, plasma monoamine oxidase & cortisol levels. ⠀⠀ _____________________
⠀⠀ ⠀⠀
the practice of kundalini yoga is believed to maintain homeostasis (equilibrium) between the sympathetic & parasympathetic activity of the nervous system and can be used in treatment of depression & other mental health issues. ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀

ahead of president trump’s second state of the union — which closely follows a 34-day government shutdown, the longest in u.s. history — the democratic women of congress all dressed in white. in a press conference shortly before the president’s address, the congresswomen delivered speeches about gender equality in the county, and how trump failed to address the issues facing so many americans. “today we stand together wearing white in solidarity with the women of the suffrage movement who refused to take no for an answer,” said representative brenda lawrence, who is also the leader of the democratic women’s working group. “to an administration that has closed its eyes to women, we will be seen.” .

text:
i was sexualized from before i even hit puberty. the sexualization of children, particularly young girls, is something that i am not alone in. this contributes to rape culture and the feelings of inevitability that most young women have that they will be cat called, harassed, and sexually assaulted at some point in their lives.
this poem tells one experience of assault, harassment, cat calling, or sexualization for every year of my life starting at the age of nine years old.  these are some of the many experiences that have shaped me into the woman i am today. 
tell me about your formative experiences in the comments below⬇️💙

text:
•• h e a l t h y •• relationship conflict resolution skills  #advocate #idaho ——————————————————————— conflict is a predictable part of virtually all relationships. it can also be a significant source of stress. therefore, with most conflicts, it’s important to find a resolution. this seems like a statement of the obvious, but many people suppress their anger or just ‘go along to get along.’ they think that by addressing a conflict, they are creating one, and simply keep quiet when upset. unfortunately, this isn’t a healthy long-term strategy. for one thing, unresolved conflict can lead to resentment and additional unresolved conflict in the relationship. even more important, ongoing conflict can actually have a negative impact on your health and longevity. 
here are some guidelines to make conflict resolution more simple and less stressful. —————————————————————— #lifestyle #family #loveshouldnthurt #december #enddv #byui #dvfacts #dancing #entrepreneur #fall #design #wellness #marketing #friends #idaho #timesup #metoo #idaho #health #breakthesilence #idaho #graphicdesign #healthy #winter #stalking #tdvam #february

text:
pope admits clerical abuse of nuns including sexual slavery

epa

pope francis made the admission while visiting the middle east

pope francis has admitted that clerics have sexually abused nuns, and in one case they were kept as sex slaves.

he said in that case his predecessor, pope benedict, was forced to shut down an entire congregation of nuns who were being abused by priests.

it is thought to be the first time that pope francis has acknowledged the sexual abuse of nuns by the clergy.

he said the church was attempting to address the problem but said it was "still going on". sex abuse and the catholic church

pope francis made the comments on tuesday to reporters while on a historic tour of the middle east.

he admitted that priests and bishops had abused nuns, but said the church was aware of the issue and "working on it". "it's a path that we've been on," he said. "pope benedict had the courage to dissolve a female congregation which was at a certain level, because this slavery of women had entered it - slavery, even to the point of sexual slavery - on the part of clerics or the founder." alessandro gisotti of the vatican press office later told cbs news that the order in question had been based in france.

pope francis said sexual abuse of nuns was an ongoing problem but happened largely in "certain congregations, predominantly new ones". last november, the catholic church's global organisation for nuns denounced the "culture of silence and secrecy" that prevented them from speaking out.

just days ago the vatican's women's magazine, women church world, condemned the abuse,saying in some cases nuns were forced to abort priests' children - something catholicism forbids.

the magazine said the #metoo movement meant more women were now coming forward with their stories.

text:
one of the things i had going for me as i set out to write my book was that i had never written anything in my life. most would think that this would be a negative thing. but just as i watch people get into my industry these days with no experience or extensive training in the field of health/wellness and have great success, this is how i saw myself writing a book. when you don’t have all of the extensive history and aren’t caught up in all of the rules of right and wrong, you operate from the heart with less fear and judgement and more freedom to be your true authentic self. and i think we need a lot more of that in our world right now. i'm excited to share my true, authentic self and message with the world.❤️
click on link 👆to order your copy of my soon-to-be released book. #victorious 📖 #vday ❤️

one of the things i had going for me as i set out to write my book was that i had never written anything in my life. most would think that this would be a negative thing. but just as i watch people get into my industry these days with no experience or extensive training in the field of health/wellness and have great success, this is how i saw myself writing a book. when you don’t have all of the extensive history and aren’t caught up in all of the rules of right and wrong, you operate from the heart with less fear and judgement and more freedom to be your true authentic self. and i think we need a lot more of that in our world right now. i am excited to share my true, authentic self and message with the world.❤️
click on link 👆to order your copy of my soon-to-be released book. #victorious 📖 #vday ❤️

text:
i have been facing a number of internal battles by myself for a very long time. recently, i found that internalizing those battles and facing defeat time after time, was doing more harm than good. i reached out. i found therapy, again. i have been finding ways to vocalize my honesty with others but most importantly myself. 5 1/2 years ago, i faced what i now understand to be something i should have never faced when i was 15. i should have never had to believe that the wrong i was being caught up in, was right. it has taken defeat after defeat to realize the need for simply being honest with myself and saying ‘hey, i’m not doing okay’. i feel compelled to share my story on a very public platform to help others understand that many smiling faces you know are facing struggles you would never know about. reach out. give others the time to ask for help. never deny a stranger a smile. 
to the people who have given me their strength to find my own strength, thank you. 
to others who may be facing horrible and isolating internal struggles; help is only a stretch of a hand away. when you feel ready, don’t be afraid to speak your truth. 
i can, with a sigh of relief, see myself healing. and for that, i am grateful. 
#metoo

text:
@classysilhouette is a #female #singer #songwriter and #producer based in #atlanta #georgia.the #queenofqueens album is an #rnb #hiphop album that was released in 2015 that introduced a #new #femalerapper & #poet nena marcella & was intended to empower females & encourage them to support each other. it has nothing to do with the city of queens.
the  album was met with a lot of bias by other male artists who must have lied to by someone who did not want anyone to recognize that a woman could be successful as a producer with her own production company/record label. many injustices were done to #classysilhouette. 
1. #computerhacking  they paid hackers to try to sabotage her project. they hacked into her software & deliberately tried to mess up the mixes of the tracks to try to make her work seem mediocre because they could not handle the #truth.
2. #slander - someone went as far as to try & smear her name by telling vicious lies so no one would want to work with her. they even went as far as to lie & say she was a transgender but this is not true. classy silhouette is a #femalefrombirth a #mother a #woman a #lady who worked very hard on all of her projects. 
3. #theftofintellectualproperty - classy silhouette didn’t understand why they were telling these lies until they began to steal her intellectual property (music tracks video treatments, lyrics out of her songs, photo concepts and graphic designs)
4. the female artist @nenamarcella was totally mistreated. she was lied on as well. because of the heaviness of her voice another female rapper went around lying to people convincing them that she was a man. but she is not. she is  a beautiful female rapper & poet & now has her own album out. click here to go to @nenamarcella’s profile & click the link in bio to listen to her music & watch videos.
5. we don’t know why someone would be this hateful to slander someone & try to defame someone’s character this way. it was a very hurtful thing but we didn’t allow that to stop progress.  #classysilhouetteproductions has released 2 more albums since then

text: ok so storytime ! this story time is from yesterday lol so i had to go somewhere and i don’t have  a car so i take pt (public transportation) anyways i’m waiting at the stop and this guy like comes out of nowhere and sits next to me which i wouldn’t have minded but he sat so fucking close like ? i knew him? and he introduces himself and i’m not rude so i said hello and he’s asking me if i need a ride or if i need anything and i’m like uh no. you woulda thought he’d leave me alone 😐 but no dude goes on to saying how i’m pretty allat bs and he’s. not. leaving. me. alone. so the bus is coming and it passes by me and i have to flag it down and dude says “you really gonna take the bus over me?” like yes sir i will cause you’re ugly and you’re old enough to be my father . so i get on the bus and i’m paying fair and he follows me onto the bus. like huh? and he’s trying to pay for me and i’m like no sir keep ur damn money and he’s still talking shit. like he’s not taking no for an answer and the whole bus is just fucking staring which is embarrassing and when i’m done paying he’s still talking and i go to sit down but like i’m mad bc i hate guys 🙄 i really do . like once i said no he shoulda just kept it moving but nah he  wanna be weird and shit.. and that type of behavior is the reason why the world is the way it is today. the reason why women risk everything when they have to come out and say #metoo it’s sad and disheartening. sorry it’s not a funny story time but this is the reality of the world we live in today.

text:
________________________________________надо жить – вопреки, даже если - невмочь.
даже если в глазах беспросветная ночь,
и дыханье спирает от боли в груди,
и лукавое время твердит: «уходи!» выпей чашу свою. что дано – до глотка.
труден путь – но дорога всегда коротка.
надо жить - потому что узнать не дано:
чем твоё завершится земное кино?

для чего ты живёшь? для кого ты – ступень?
чем бесценен и значим твой прожитый день?
и в смятенье своём, и в бездонной тиши
надо жить, совершая работу души.

не бояться прослыть дураком, чудаком.
открываться и зреть с каждым новым витком.
это - долг, это - шанс, это - уровень твой.
всё с тобой. всё возможно, пока ты живой.

и в сплетенье судеб, в каждом шаге – ответ
«для чего?» это воля , и суть, и завет.
в ткани жизни – твоя судьбоносная нить.
и во имя , и ради её – надо жить! ольга альтовская.

и в смятенье своём, и в бездонной тиши
надо жить, совершая работу души.

не бояться прослыть дураком, чудаком.
открываться и зреть с каждым новым витком.
это - долг, это - шанс, это - уровень твой.
всё с тобой. всё возможно, пока ты живой.

и в сплетенье судеб, в каждом шаге – ответ
«для чего?» это воля , и суть, и завет.
в ткани жизни – твоя судьбоносная нить.
и во имя , и ради её – надо жить! ольга альтовская.

text:
the eleventh submission to the survivor tree project comes from nishea balajadia. from a very young age, nishea suffered prolonged sexual abuse at the hands of her grandfather; and like so many other childhood survivors, her innocent young mind coped with her trauma by suppressing her memories until adulthood. though many years had passed by the time she was able to recall what had happened to her, she reported her abuse. and when she did, several other relatives came forward to describe similar experiences at the hands of the same man. her abuser was brought to trial, pled out, and was convicted. •
the part of nishea’s story that touched me the most- and moved me to tears- was when she spoke about the day of sentencing. she and a handful of other survivors confronted their abuser with impact statements, given in front of a packed courtroom as the judge wept. though her abuser’s sentence was disproportionate to his crimes, she described experiencing an overwhelming feeling of love that day. “it was a testament and affirmation that my abuse does not define me and it does not hold me back from the love i can give.” nishea’s story is one of pure courage. she spoke her truth- loudly, unashamedly- and inspired others to come forward as well. surrounded by loved ones, she stood before her abuser and spoke of moving on. of not being defined by what he had done to her. of still being able to love. thank you, nishea, for sharing your truth and your strength. to survivors who have not reported, your story is truly an inspiration. and i know that this world is a better place for the love you give. ✨🌱 click the link in my bio if others would like to contribute their story to #thesurvivortreeproject. #survivor #survivoradvocate #believesurvivors #believewomen #believeblackwomen #rapesurvivor #sexualabuse #childhoodsexualabuse #csasurvivor#metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement #thesurvivortreeproject #artist

a toutes celles qui ont besoin d'insta pour engendrer narcisse ou lui donner à manger, l'art therapie te décolle de l'image du corps puis te recolles pour qu'enfin tu re-touches ton corps... juste toi... plus tu te montres, moins on te voit...

text:
truth time tuesday!! (because the transformation is in progress!) i slacked over the holidays...i ate crap and drank more wine than was healthy. 😬

i used food for comfort to cope with separation/divorce. 😞

i got frustrated with not seeing the results others got.
and that made me:
i stopped moving my body daily with my weightlifting, dancing and then winter hit and away went my daily walking. 😑

i knew what i should be doing.😳 i kept saying tomorrow i’ll get back on track...only to see tomorrow turn into day after day and still no effort to show up for myself.🤦‍♀️ i kept expecting a miracle and getting frustrated with the lack of results, so i had a running tape saying ... “why bother? you always fail anyways or that only happens for others not me.” 😑

and then i stepped on the scale because my clothes had began to get tighter...😳🤦‍♀️😡😑
and that was eye opener! i’d gained back 20 of the 60lbs i’d lost! 😡🤦‍♀️😳😡 so here is me being real and truthful. 😇

i’m human. i struggle just like you. 
i’m not perfect and i fail too. 
but, unlike many of you, now i have tools that help me get results.😇🙏😇 i understand what it takes to get results and i will get back to where i was and further. i believe in the power of me. 🔥👸 failing is feedback, not forever!😊🎉 did you give up when you learned how to walk? probably not, so apply that same tenacity to understanding your unique body and all the truths it’s trying to reveal to you. 🙏

if you’re struggling with knowing what will really work for you...reach out to me! i have an entire collection of resources to help you too!!🙏🎉🙏 and i want you to know what i know...
“everything is possible and there is always a way, but focus on the why, not the how! 🎉

that’s where i help you! 
the right system👌
the right support👌
the right accountability👌

while there’s a lot of great programs out there that are effective, many are not. programs that get the best results quickly includes three things, take away any one of those three things and it fails.😡😬😳 that’s what i did to myself. 
i had the right system... but no support and no accountability!🤦‍♀️😳🤦‍♀️
see how that works? 🤔

text:
it's a few days ago, when alexis from the blog @stump_kitchen posted the story “you are so beautiful, but... your arm.” this was shared several times and other bloggers like pia from @gotta_hand_it_to_her added their story, too. to make these incidents public, is absolutely very important. we've seen how impactful the #metoo - story was.
in this case the problem might be, that it all remains in its echo chamber. although the blog itself, supporting blogs and e.g. the great community of the @lucky_fin_project have a respectable reach in social media, i fear that it does not carry so much into the public section to get the necessary attention and starting a social discussion about such a behavior.
the point is, that if you're discriminated because of a weakness (and that includes racism and sexism as well),you can make it clear and tell how much you feel discriminated, offended and hurt. but at the end you need support from the other side.
the first thing and that is happening with the latest posts from all these blogs, is to raise awareness, but we have to bring it out of this echo chamber. there are a lot of people, who don't see the problem that clear and a lot of people who just look away. although the named cases here are obviously best examples for bad behavior, there are a lot of hidden discriminations as well. 
i for myself learned a lot about hidden discrimination in our speech, in terms and phrases in the last time. 
the second step is confrontation and for this we need a kind of allies. in all this examples, i guess a discussion between the discriminated person and the person who discriminates, is assumingly fruitless. but if someone - seemingly without that weakness - comes to stand at your side, the situation will change, because those people don't like publicity.
what we need is something like #iamyourally . this does not mean, that anybody has a personal ally. it means, that we need people, who see themselves as a part of a movement and whenever they notice such a situation, they will stand at your side.
name: thoughts on difference

text:
#cancelled: disillusionment in the age of twitter #metoo
#
the overlap in the sets of ‘good people’ and ‘famous people’ seems to diminish every day. chip by chip veneers of morality in the film and music industry are fragmenting to reveal the darker reality of the human capacity to cause pain. it’s this process that reminds us that bad words and actions are ubiquitous, with the entertainment industry only serving as a zone of magnification for how temporary illusions of virtue are. this is not to say that we are inherently bad, but rather an acknowledgement of the fact that, unavoidably, all of us have said or done bad things of a different scale- the mistakes of the rich and famous just have a greater staying power. in many ways, the deconstruction of the notion of artistic genius that obscures much judgement of problematic or criminal actions is a blessing. a year on from rebecca hall, timothée chalamet and selena gomez’s denouncement of woody allen and declaration that they would donate their salaries from his (now shelved) film a rainy day in new york to more formal campaign movements such as time’s up, we can begin to recognise the force of good that public scrutiny can be in amplifying…
link: http://metoozoo.com/news/cancelled-disillusionment-in-the-age-of-twitter-metoo/

text:
register for *safety stars early* february 10, 2019, cols, oh

protect your child from harm and gain valuable tools for building better relationships. children together with their adults learn age-appropriate safety skills and how to practice them as a team. we introduce skills that children can use every day to feel safer and more confident in dealing with people at home, on the playground, and out and about in the world. 
pre-registration is required as there is limited space. the cost is for one child and one caring adult. each additional child will be an additional $25 per child.
this workshop is not appropriate for infants or children younger than 5 years old. please arrange child care prior to the workshop.
